Description
       John McNeil Studio is looking for a developer candidate that can
       wear multiple hats – someone who has a strong background in Web QA,
       but also some experience and interest in doing front end web
       development.
       In QA mode, you will be responsible for the testing and quality
       assurance of high-profile websites and interactive advertising
       campaigns and will be checking for proper functionality, content
       and layout consistency. In front-end development, you will work on
       building interactive web experiences and perfectly styling them to
       match beautifully designed comps. The ideal candidate will have
       strong attention to detail, a creative eye, and love good design.
       Required skills:
       * Experience with manual and automated testing on the web across a
       variety of platforms
       * Experience writing and executing test plans
       * Knowledge of testing frameworks and tools
       * Meticulous attention to detail (we're obsessed with our UI being
       just right)
       * Experience implementing designs in standards compliant HTML & CSS
       * Familiarity with JavaScript
       * Passion for good design and usability on the web
       Nice to have:
       * Experience testing on mobile devices
       * Experience testing/building responsive websites
       * Experience developing automated QA testing processes from scratch
       * Experience using JS Frameworks/Libraries (jQuery, Bootstrap.js,
       Backbone.js, Underscore.js)
       * Experience with Ruby on Rails, PHP, or Node.js (Most of our
       full-stack apps are Rails)
       * Knowledge of Wordpress theme or plugin development
